International tuna conservation bodies are meeting in Kobe, Japan to address overfishing concerns.
Japan faces a quota cut for southern bluefin tuna due to overfishing.
The global catch of bluefin tuna in the Mediterranean has been reduced to prevent depletion.
Environmentalists urge radical changes in fishing practices to save tuna stocks.
A global action plan is expected to be adopted to monitor and manage tuna populations.
Participants aim to establish a tracking system for tuna origin to combat illegal fishing.
The conference seeks sustainable management of tuna fisheries to prevent collapse and extinction.
